{
  "texts": [
    "Accordingly, our results highlight the need for policies and strategies that promote capability innovation-such as grants, recognition programs, or targeted challenges for new feature development.",
    "This approach could create a balance between human ingenuity and LLM capabilities, utilizing the strengths of each to drive a varied and impactful innovation scene, even as LLMs continue to advance.",
    "Such interventions, particularly valuable in voluntary collaborative settings, could help maintain a healthy balance between iterative enhancement and capability expansion as LLMs continue to advance.",
    "They might also address potential trade-offs between productivity gains and human capital development (Agrawal et al. 2023) by ensuring that human creativity remains valued alongside LLM-assisted efficiency.",
    "Our research also has implications for organizations that participate in or encourage employee contributions to open-source projects."
  ]
}